  const post = getPost(req.body.id);
}
```

2. **Use the `req.params` object instead of the `req.body` object.** The `req.params` object contains the query parameters that were passed to the route. In your case, the `id` query parameter is used to identify the post that you want to delete. You can use the `req.params` object to get the `id` of the post and then use that to get the post from the database.

```
